                    <comment id="12609235" author="rengels@ix.netcom.com" created="Mon, 30 Jun 2008 14:58:38 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This comment is very misleading.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since there is IO involved, any operation can block, which will lower CPU utilization.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You just need to make sure that the locks control different physical resources.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12609708" author="jasonrutherglen" created="Tue, 1 Jul 2008 21:57:02 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;lucene-1322.patch&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CSIndexInput.clone() added that clones the base IndexInput removing the synchronization overhead from CompoundFileReader.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
